						<summary>

						<p>On the four faces of a pillar in the same place.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1060 = 1138 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The details of date given in the record namely Śaka 1060, Uttarāyaṇa do not admit for verification.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of 55 sheep by Pedda-Koṇḍapa-nāyaka, son of Paṟiti Nāvi-nāyaka, for maintaing a lamp. </p>						

						</summary>
